cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

The paper deals with video recognition models and learning video representations using pre-trained image models. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of deep learning techniques and transfer learning, which are common in the sub-categories cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also deals with multimedia data, which falls under the sub-category cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper discusses the use of distillation frameworks, which is a technique commonly used in the sub-category cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
